# Git commits

When creating or amending commits on behalf of the user:

- **Never** add `Co-authored-by:`, `Signed-off-by:` for Cursor, or any AI/IDE co-author line unless the user explicitly asks for it.
- **Never** finish `/auto-commit` (or any agent commit) if the message or trailers mention Cursor as co-author.
- The commit message must contain only what the user requested (Conventional Commits subject/body, etc.).
- Scope `chore(cursor)` in the subject is allowed (project tooling); that is not co-authorship.

## Cursor trailers injected by the IDE or hooks

Cursor (or a git hook) may append lines the agent did **not** write, for example:

```text
Co-authored-by: Cursor <cursoragent@cursor.com>
```

**Treat that as a failed commit** until the message is clean.

### Mandatory check after every commit

```bash
git log -1 --format=%B
```

If the output contains `Co-authored-by: Cursor`, `cursoragent@cursor.com`, or any Cursor co-author trailer → **rewrite before push**.

### How to rewrite (unpushed commits only)

Prefer **`git commit-tree`** when `git commit` / `--amend` keeps re-injecting the trailer:

```bash
MSG="$(git log -1 --format=%B | sed '/^Co-authored-by: Cursor/d')"
TREE=$(git rev-parse HEAD^{tree})
PARENT=$(git rev-parse HEAD^)
NEW=$(printf '%s\n' "$MSG" | git commit-tree "$TREE" -p "$PARENT")
git reset --hard "$NEW"
git log -1 --format=%B   # must NOT show Cursor
```

Alternative if amend works without re-injection:

```bash
git commit --amend -F msg.txt
git log -1 --format=%B
```

### Push policy

- If `Co-authored-by: Cursor` appears on **unpushed** commits, rewrite the message before push; do not leave it on `main`.
- **Do not** `git push --force` to rewrite history unless the user explicitly requests it.

- **Never** restore deleted files or lines before committing unless the user explicitly asks; deletions are usually intentional.

See also `.cursor/commands/auto-commit.md` (section «eliminar menciones de Cursor»).
